         (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>.)
       </span>
      </p>

     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA10d010n1-ptr" id="PJA10d010n1">1</a>
      
   <p>For the forged letter from Gen. Henry Clinton and a brief history of its publication, see <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s letter of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-09-02-0209" class="document">21 May</a> to C. W. F. Dumas, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-09-02-0209&amp;expandNote=PJA09d228n1#PJA09d228n1" class="document">note 1</a> (above).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA10d010n2-ptr" id="PJA10d010n2">2</a>
      
   <p>That is, Vergennes and Gabriel de Sartine. See <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s letter of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-09-02-0309-0002" class="document">13 July</a> to Vergennes, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-09-02-0309-0002&amp;expandNote=PJA09d353n1#PJA09d353n1" class="document">note
       1</a> (above); and Vergennes reply of the <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-10-02-0011-0001-0002" class="document">20th</a> (below).</p>

